  "prompt": "What's the meaning of ISO?",
  "response": "ISO stands for the International Organization for Standardization. It is an independent, non-governmental international organization that develops and publishes standards to ensure quality, safety, efficiency, and interoperability of products, services, and systems across various industries worldwide. The term \"ISO\" is derived from the Greek word \"isos,\" meaning \"equal,\" reflecting the organization's aim to standardize and harmonize practices globally.",
